of blood in the urine.
It doesn't fit.

600
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:22,044
I'm interested in things
that don't fit.

601
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:24,054
Tell me why you did it.

602
00:35:28,659 --> 00:35:31,822
Your other victims
you were almost
bragging about.

603
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:35,231
What was different
about this guy?

604
00:35:39,537 --> 00:35:41,971
It happened
when I was in gen pop.

605
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:47,266
I was in the library,
just reading.

606
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:54,114
And I started feeling
real nervous.
This guy was staring at me.

607
00:35:54,552 --> 00:35:58,283
I could feel his eyes
digging holes
in the back of my neck.

608
00:35:59,023 --> 00:36:00,684
Made me feel crazy.

609
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:05,094
Sweat was
pouring down my face.

610
00:36:06,197 --> 00:36:10,327
I could hear my heartbeat
racing in my ears.

611
00:36:13,204 --> 00:36:15,434
I just raged out on the dude.

612
00:36:21,379 --> 00:36:23,574
So what's the differential
for raging out?

613
00:36:23,648 --> 00:36:26,412
Excess testosterone, steroids.
Adrenalin?

614
00:36:26,984 --> 00:36:29,748
Prep Clarence for surgery.
Care to share with the class?

615
00:36:29,820 --> 00:36:33,813
Oh, come on,
do I have to spell it out
for you? Pheochromocytoma.

616
00:36:34,425 --> 00:36:36,290
Actually, I'm not sure
how you spell it.

617
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,987
But you said it yourself,
adrenalin.

618
00:36:38,062 --> 00:36:40,553
Pheochromocytoma sits on top
of the adrenal gland,

619
00:36:40,631 --> 00:36:43,065
randomly spits out
oodles of the stuff.
It's perfect.

620
00:36:43,134 --> 00:36:46,661
It explains everything, the
tachycardia, pulmonary edema,
the vasoconstriction that

621
00:36:46,737 --> 00:36:47,999
caused the necrotic bowel.

622
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:50,905
Even explains
how he had the strength
to rip the rail off his bed.

623
00:36:50,975 --> 00:36:53,671
But pheo's extremely rare.
I love rare.

624
00:36:54,111 --> 00:36:56,671
Set up an MRl.
Where's Cameron?

625
00:36:58,149 --> 00:36:59,810
Like I don't know.

626
00:37:01,452 --> 00:37:03,044
(WOMAN LAUGHlNG)

627
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:04,883
(BOTH CHATTERlNG)

628
00:37:05,456 --> 00:37:08,016
Dr. Cameron, could l
borrow you for a consult?

629
00:37:08,092 --> 00:37:10,993
Bittersweet thing
about being head
of the Oncology Department,

630
00:37:11,062 --> 00:37:13,587
I get cc'd on all
the biopsy results.

631
00:37:13,664 --> 00:37:15,029
Yeah, I know.

632
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:18,525
She's terminal.
Yeah.

633
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:22,261
So I take it you were
in there informing her?

634
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:26,071
Well, I hadn't exactly
gotten around to that,
but I was just...

635
00:37:26,143 --> 00:37:28,407
Doing what? Making friends?

636
00:37:30,481 --> 00:37:31,675
Cindy's divorced.

637
00:37:31,749 --> 00:37:34,684
She doesn't have any kids,
no siblings,
both her parents are gone...

638
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:38,188
It's not your job
to be her friend!
Do you understand?

639
00:37:38,289 --> 00:37:40,120
And it's not worth it.

640
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:44,591
She feels better her final
few days, and you're not
the same, maybe for years.

641
00:37:44,662 --> 00:37:48,257
You don't think it's worth it?
I know it's not worth it.

642
00:37:53,237 --> 00:37:54,727
My husband...

643
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:04,138
I met him just after
he was diagnosed
with terminal brain cancer.

644
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:09,452
If I hadn't married him...
He was alone.

645
00:38:10,888 --> 00:38:15,120
When a good person dies,
there should be an impact
on the world.

646
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:17,894
Somebody should notice.

647
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,420
Somebody should be upset.

648
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:26,802
"Pheo" what?

649
00:38:27,738 --> 00:38:29,603
I don't even remember.

650
00:38:29,674 --> 00:38:33,735
It's just a fancy way
of saying "small,
adrenalin-secreting tumor."

651
00:38:34,612 --> 00:38:36,842
Yeah,
that clarified it for you.

652
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:41,445
All you need to know is,
if I'm right, we can fix it.

653
00:38:41,519 --> 00:38:43,544
Just gotta find it first.

654
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:45,580
We need an MRl.

655
00:38:45,856 --> 00:38:48,051
It's completely painless
for most people.

656
00:38:48,125 --> 00:38:49,649
But not for me?

657
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:52,724
I assume you got
those tattoos in prison.

658
00:38:53,464 --> 00:38:56,661
